(690, 5, '2016-01-11 22:25:49', '2016-01-11 22:25:49', '<p style="text-align: center;">The time is almost here!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"> We are excited to announce that we will be running a booth at KBIS 2016 for another year along with 20,000+ other industry professionals from around the globe!</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_659" align="aligncenter" width="1280"]<a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Kbis-Booth.jpg" rel="ProHoods/ Proline Range Hoods Booth Set up 2015"><img class="wp-image-659 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Kbis-Booth.jpg" alt="Proline Range Hoods ProHoods KBIS 2015 Booth Set Up 2015" width="1280" height="960" /></a> Booth Set up for KBIS Last Year[/caption]\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">For those of you who have not heard of <strong>KBIS</strong>, it is one of the worlds largest gatherings focused on new ideas, products, and technologies of design, building and remodeling. Attendees will have access to the newest and the greatest products, more industry leading brands, and more opportunities to network. The Conference will be January <strong>19th-22nd </strong>in Las Vegas, and you are not too late to register, so get your tickets while they are available! We are looking forward to meeting others in the industry including architects, builders, cabinet shops, consultants, dealers, designers, distributers, students, and more! We will also be having a drawing and GIVING AWAY A <strong>FREE RANGE HOOD </strong>to one lucky winner. Its going to be a great time and an event that you definitely won''t want to miss!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Will you be Attending KBIS 2016?</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>"It’s like fashion week for the kitchen and bath industry and so important to attend in order to keep up with what’s new and trending."</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>-Justin Anders-Henne, Interior Designer, Grayling Construction</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Join us at the world’s largest international trade event focused exclusively on all things kitchen and bath along with the industry’s leading manufacturers.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.kbis.com/" target="_blank">Register today</a> to attend the Kitchen &amp; Bath Industry Show and join us in Las Vegas or follow along with the hashtag<strong> #KBIS2016. </strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>We hope to see you there! </strong></p>\r\n&nbsp;', 'Will you be Attending KBIS 2016?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '656-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-01-11 22:25:49', '2016-01-11 22:25:49', '', 656, 'http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/656-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(595, 1, '2015-12-10 22:47:09', '2015-12-10 22:47:09', '<p style="text-align: center;">Have you ever walked into a persons home that you just met recently, and you instantly felt like you could tell  a lot about what kind of person they are just by the way their home looks and feels? It''s important to not judge a book by its cover, but at the same time first impressions are  <strong>EVERYTHING</strong>. Every design and style of the home should reflect the homeowner’s personality and bring a particular feeling to everyone who comes to visit. From countertops to hardwood floors, from paint colors to accessories, no element should be added without your personal identity. Have you ever thought of your Kitchen this way, relating to your own personal identity? It’s now time to see what your Kitchen Style really says about you!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Which category do you fit in to? Let us know in the comments box below! Join the fun and <strong>SUBSCRIBE</strong> to this blog for more fun content as we celebrate cooking, celebrations, and everything <strong>KITCHEN</strong>.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong> Cottage/ Shabby-Chic Style - </strong>You are cheerful, laid back and welcoming. You can never get enough of fresh cut flowers to set on your table, and feel that it''s the simple things like this in life that make you the happiest. Your small kitchen doesn''t bother you, and you are completely content making the best use of space with what you do have. You are a maximizer, earnestly trying to make things better than their original state. You are immensely talented and believe in the value of being a good homemaker. You love decorating with trinkets and accessories that feel like home and mean something -whether thats by hanging your grandmothers favorite plates on your wall, or by hanging your hand-knitted towel beside the sink. You love to tell stories and treasure many memories -you could only hope for others who visit to hold on to sweet moments shared in your home. Your guests love to come over because being in your home feels like a GIANT HUG. It is important to you that your guests feel welcomed and loved.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/3e4eac32a67724c803306916776e054a1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-303 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/3e4eac32a67724c803306916776e054a1.jpg" alt="3e4eac32a67724c803306916776e054a" width="606" height="713" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Photo Credit: <a href="http://www.myhomeideas.com">www.myhomeideas.com</a></strong><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/84c369175f62349d0e7317598c6396891.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-304 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/84c369175f62349d0e7317598c6396891.jpg" alt="84c369175f62349d0e7317598c639689" width="611" height="752" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Photo Credit: <a href="http://www.ourboathouse.com">www.ourboathouse.com</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Modern/Contemporary &amp; Clean - </strong>You are not a fan of ornate flourishes or having your home feel raffish in any sort. When people come into your home they feel a silent confidence that is intriguing. You find yourself leaning always towards design choices that involve clean straight lines, and neutral textures and colors. You love black and white and only using minimal colors as focal points such as abstract wall art. You can''t stand cluttered countertops and constantly feel the need keep your counter clean with little to nothing on top. You are a minimalist and in order for you to feel content and relaxed in your space you must keep things simple. You focus on the essentials instead of the fluff. You are a realist and can look at situations for what they really are. In your head, dreaming visionary thoughts never got anyone anywhere, hard work did. You love the look and feel of natural materials such as wood, leather, teak and linen. You believe that "less is more" and live for simplicity in everything. You are an efficient go-getter type person. You are a socialite, and an entertainer and people look up to you for your successes.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/8fd45869dea2981e4b46a823f5e37d591.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-305 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/8fd45869dea2981e4b46a823f5e37d591.jpg" alt="8fd45869dea2981e4b46a823f5e37d59" width="628" height="846" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Photo Credit: <a href="http://www.feedinspiration.com">www.feedinspiration.com</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/302a4ae5038ec4b4ae76d9c41affdce31.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-306 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/302a4ae5038ec4b4ae76d9c41affdce31.jpg" alt="302a4ae5038ec4b4ae76d9c41affdce3" width="736" height="1102" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong> Photo Credit: <a href="https://www.homestratosphere.com/kitchen-island-ideas/" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">homestratosphere.com</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Transitional Mix -</strong> You could not possibly make up your mind to decorate with only contemporary or traditional styles, that is why you need to have a mix of BOTH. If Goldilocks were decorating a house, transitional style would check all of her "just right" boxes: not too cold, not too formal, not too fussy. Your style is classic with a contemporary twist. You love a neutral balance of colors such as taupe, tan and vanilla to evoke a clean, serene atmosphere using color minimally. You prefer textural touches over excessive loud decor and froofy accents. You do not feel the need to decorate excessively and would rather keep the focus on the simplicity and sophistication of the design. You love the look of a clean, un-cluttered counter space against your beautiful chocolate traditional cabinets. You feel the need to balance both masculine and feminine attributes for a comfortable and relaxing, uncomplicated design that both genders, guys and gals in your family can enjoy. You''re a natural diplomat. You prefer a few statement accessories to layers of necklaces and wristfuls of bracelets. You serve mac and cheese on your wedding china. Your dream vacation involves chilling out at an elegant spa. You can''t understand why people think beige is boring. You live a hectic busy schedule and that is why you have designed your home around relaxation, so when you get back you can slip off your shoes, take a deep breath and feel at ease.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/1092e5454d5e1dff5bf18acd868dc9571.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-307 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/1092e5454d5e1dff5bf18acd868dc9571.jpg" alt="1092e5454d5e1dff5bf18acd868dc957" width="633" height="783" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Photo Credit: <a href="http://www.the36thavenue.com/kitchen-design-tips/" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">the36thavenue.com</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/3eda47c0772dca65611ab8c6e675f6e11.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-308 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/3eda47c0772dca65611ab8c6e675f6e11.jpg" alt="3eda47c0772dca65611ab8c6e675f6e1" width="642" height="526" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Photo Credit: <a href="http://www.homebunch.com/transitional-farmhouse-design/" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">homebunch.com</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Eclectic Style - </strong>You are someone who is fascinated by the significance of different cultures and history and that is why you choose to design your space with combined elements or particular styles from different time periods and different origins. You live for the story behind each piece and love sharing these stories with others.  You are a harmonizer and that is why you designed your home that way, to enhance and contribute to the significance and beauty of one piece with the other. You want your home to feel artistic, and exquisite, like a piece of extraordinary work. To you it is not ridiculous to pay an extensive price to get those custom hand carved bar stools that were found from the remains of a profound event in history, or to bring back the perfect hand woven, Persion rug that caught your eye as you were traveling over seas. You are a person that believes in the power of significance and that some things should be put on a pedestal as they are worth every ounce of thoughtfulness. You love attention, but you are also a good listener and value the importance and story of why people are they way they are, and live the way that they live. You are a people person, an entertainer, and a story teller.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/a8349274d941f1068014a8f84cb3f3561.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-309 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/a8349274d941f1068014a8f84cb3f3561.jpg" alt="a8349274d941f1068014a8f84cb3f356" width="736" height="920" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Photo Credit: <a href="http://www.casasugar.com/Celebrity-Kitchens-34083768" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">casasugar.com</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/0bbf40982ffe958be804d4ebf95b9dc31.jpg"><img class="wp-image-310" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/0bbf40982ffe958be804d4ebf95b9dc31.jpg" alt="0bbf40982ffe958be804d4ebf95b9dc3" width="616" height="802" /></a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>  Photo Credit: <a href="http://www.sfgirlbybay.com/2015/01/05/lets-start-with-eclectic-color/" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">sfgirlbybay.com</a></strong><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/c58bf5cc81174262b4709d820a16b08a1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-311 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/c58bf5cc81174262b4709d820a16b08a1.jpg" alt="c58bf5cc81174262b4709d820a16b08a" width="540" height="736" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Photo Credit: <a href="http://www.thekitchn.com/get-the-look-opulent-hollywood-kitchen-style-renovation-resources-184119" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">thekitchn.com</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Country/Farmhouse Style - </strong>To you the simple country life is the best life. You don''t understand the glamorous idea of living in a big city, you would much rather have a big yard that your kids can run and play in, a garden to grow your fruits and veggies in, and live in a quite community far away from any boisterous late night extravaganza''s and loud festivities. To you a city that never sleeps sound horrific, you count on that precious time when you can have a cup of tea, read a book, and fall into a nice deep sleep. You are completely obsessed with your farmhouse sink and cleaning dirty dishes is actually fun for you because of it. Family means everything to you and you look forward to that time every evening that you can gather as a family and share a home cooked meal around the table. You love to decorate using gentle, light hues that feel cheerful and pleasantly homy. You love your classic, uncomplicated furnishings and the distressed look just shows that you put each of your items to good use. You are frugal, and do not feel the need to live loud. You know what is truly important, and to you that is family.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/c12fdba9be084e8fabafdfcfe4d605a41.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-312 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/c12fdba9be084e8fabafdfcfe4d605a41.jpg" alt="c12fdba9be084e8fabafdfcfe4d605a4" width="736" height="1104" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Photo Credit: <a href="http://farmhouse5540.blogspot.com/2015/01/hand-made-christmas-presents.html" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">farmhouse5540.blogspot.com</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/1a952588f3f7691f9a4c5fec39da05c31.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-313 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/1a952588f3f7691f9a4c5fec39da05c31.jpg" alt="1a952588f3f7691f9a4c5fec39da05c3" width="613" height="772" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Photo Credit: <a href="http://www.thecottagemarket.com/2013/05/25-open-shelving-kitchens.html" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">thecottagemarket.com</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Earthy Tuscan/ Rustic Style -  </strong>Your kitchen is classic, while highlighting its natural beauty and rugged, resilient spirit. Our ancestors would get a good laugh out of how fashionable the "rustic" look is today — they probably dreamed of plastered walls instead of rough logs and carpets instead of bare plank floors. But thanks to the rustic style''s roots, organic textures and shapes, and natural warmth, is becoming as popular in the heart of the city as it is out in the woods.  You can''t help but feel a sense of connection to the past that''s hard to resist. You love the idea in living in a much simpler time. You celebrate the art of repurposing. In a world where so much is virtual, you love the bold, realness that the earthy rustic style emanates. You were happiest playing in the mud as a kid. You still read old books like <i>Little House on the Prairie, and Anne of Green Gables. </i>You sleep in your sweetie''s old flannel shirts. And lets just completely forget the faux trend —  because you''ll stick to real wood, thank you.<strong>\r\n</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/56271cbddc1a9b4dba582a41cf9704a61.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-314 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/56271cbddc1a9b4dba582a41cf9704a61.jpg" alt="56271cbddc1a9b4dba582a41cf9704a6" width="591" height="554" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Photo Credit: <a href="http://dimplesandtangles.blogspot.com/search?updated-max=2013-06-14T08:10:00-05:00&amp;max-results=5&amp;start=20&amp;by-date=false" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">dimplesandtangles.blogspot.com</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/78f74b81ec173cad179cb9179e680a1c1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-315 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/78f74b81ec173cad179cb9179e680a1c1.jpg" alt="78f74b81ec173cad179cb9179e680a1c" width="600" height="450" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Photo Credit: <a href="http://www.hgtv.com/kitchens/rustic-kitchen-cabinets/index.html" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">hgtv.com</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Traditional -</strong> Your home is a quaint and comfortable one. You are a reserved person, and don''t feel the need to "get with the times" because the classics have always worked beautifully. You are a person that prefers quality over quantity. Chaos of any sort makes you queasy. Your favorite movies are the classics, untouched by Technicolor. You''ve vacationed in the same spot since you were 12. Your ideal day involves a bookshelf full of classic novels while you sip on a glass of fresh squeezed orange juice. You love the look of symmetry, artful accessories, rich wood tones, and beautiful trim. You value the advice of your elders, and try to emulate what has worked in the past in your own life. You are a clear thinker, responsible and an extremely hard worker.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/539e07834b7b2d0d3b3d0a703ce73da81.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-316 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/539e07834b7b2d0d3b3d0a703ce73da81.jpg" alt="539e07834b7b2d0d3b3d0a703ce73da8" width="591" height="576" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Photo Credit: <a href="http://www.houzz.com/photos/traditional/kitchen/p/252" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">houzz.com</a></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/45c97b802873aae6cb431f74be0919481.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-317 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/45c97b802873aae6cb431f74be0919481.jpg" alt="45c97b802873aae6cb431f74be091948" width="560" height="721" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Photo Credit: <a href="http://evolutionofstyleblog.blogspot.com/2014/01/tips-tricks-for-painting-oak-cabinets.html" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">evolutionofstyleblog.blogspot.com</a></strong></p>', 'What Does Your Kitchen Style Say About You?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '302-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-12-10 22:47:09', '2015-12-10 22:47:09', '', 302, 'http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/?p=595', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(632, 1, '2015-12-11 17:45:50', '2015-12-11 17:45:50', '<p style="text-align: center;">Its the first day of October..</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">The nights are getting darker, the goblins are coming out,</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">the witches and black cats are prowling about.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Magic is in the air, the leaves are falling,</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">The wolves in the mountains are calling.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">The time is NOW to celebrate this spooky season</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Don''t just celebrate within reason</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">What is Halloween without caldrons, costumes and candy?</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Let us help you by sharing Festive Halloween Treats that should come in handy.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">So what are you waiting for? Invite some friends over, find a spooky fun playlist, carve some pumpkins, make a spell!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"> Let us know which Halloween treat is your favorite in the comments box below! Don''t forget to subscribe! Enjoy!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/eb642f71885a0bd4fa6ac5e131b704c31.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-322 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/eb642f71885a0bd4fa6ac5e131b704c31.jpg" alt="eb642f71885a0bd4fa6ac5e131b704c3" width="580" height="1952" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.justataste.com/halloween-frankenstein-marshmallow-pops-recipe/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">Halloween Frankenstein Marshmallow Pops - Justataste.com</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/pumpkin-dirt-pudding-2-731x10241.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-323 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/