g.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/candy-corn-cupcake1.jpg" alt="candy-corn-cupcake" width="615" height="557" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.the-girl-who-ate-everything.com/2011/10/candy-corn-cupcakes.html" target="_blank">Candy Corn Cupcakes -The Girl Who Ate Everything</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/candycorn21.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-331 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/candycorn21.jpg" alt="candycorn2" width="750" height="1048" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.nelliebellie.com/candy-corn-punch-halloween-snacks/" target="_blank">Candy Corn Punch - Nellie Bellie</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Halloween-Mummy-Cupcakes1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-332" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Halloween-Mummy-Cupcakes1.jpg" alt="Halloween-Mummy-Cupcakes" width="711" height="483" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://apumpkinandaprincess.com/2013/10/halloween-treats-kids.html" target="_blank">Mummy Cupcakes - A Pumpkin and A Princess</a></p>', 'Festive Halloween Treats', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '321-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-12-11 17:45:50', '2015-12-11 17:45:50', '', 321, 'http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/?p=632', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(591, 1, '2015-12-10 22:21:53', '2015-12-10 22:21:53', '<p style="text-align: center;">It''s that wonderful, magical time of year, Wishing you happiness, joy, and cheer.\r\nMay all your days be warm and bright,\r\nAnd your nights enhanced by holiday light.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Enjoy your delectable holiday foods,\r\nAs parties and gifts create holiday moods.\r\nFavorite people play a meaningful part,\r\nWhile treasured rituals warm your heart.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Just when you thought this dish couldn''t look any more delicious, this Holiday Dessert</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">not only has a TO DIE FOR lemony cream filling and fresh berries, but it''s also Gluten-free!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">This is one Holiday Dessert that is a guaranteed winner!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Enjoy this No-Bake Chocolate Raspberry Cheesecake delight.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">May it fill your bellies and taste just right.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Dig in! </strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Raspberry-Chocolate-Cheesecake.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-404 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Raspberry-Chocolate-Cheesecake.jpg" alt="37385_l" width="851" height="612" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Ingredients </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="ingredient-table" style="text-align: left;">\r\n	<li> <label for="ingredient-0-0">2 x 160g pkt Macro Gluten-free Double Chocolate Biscuits</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-1">80g butter, melted, cooled</label> <label for="ingredient-0-2">375g cream cheese, at room temperature</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-3">125ml (1/2 cup) thickened cream</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-4">70g (1/3 cup) caster sugar</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-5">1 lemon, rind finely grated</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-6">1 tbs gelatine powder</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-7">60ml (1/4 cup) boiling water</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-8">300g fresh raspberries</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-9">60g dark chocolate melts, melted</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-10">Fresh baby mint sprigs, to serve</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-11">Pure icing sugar, to dust</label></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Directions</strong>\r\n<div class="module-content">\r\n<div class="content-item tab-content current method-tab-content">\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li class="methods" style="text-align: left;">\r\n<p class="description">Process biscuits and butter in a food processor until well combined. Press over the base and sides of a 2.5cm-deep, 13 x 36cm rectangular fluted tart tin with removable base. Freeze for 15 minutes or until firm.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li class="methods" style="text-align: left;">\r\n<p class="description">Use electric beaters to beat cream cheese, cream, sugar and lemon rind until well combined and sugar has dissolved. In a small jug, sprinkle gelatine over boiling water and whisk until dissolved. Add to cheese mixture and beat until smooth.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li class="methods" style="text-align: left;">\r\n<p class="description">Fold through 200g raspberries. Spoon into tin. Chill in fridge for 4 hours or until set.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li class="methods" style="text-align: left;">\r\n<p class="description">Meanwhile, line a tray with baking paper. Dip the tips of remaining raspberries into chocolate and place on tray to set.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li class="methods" style="text-align: left;">\r\n<p class="description">Top the cheesecake with chocolate raspberries and mint. Dust with icing sugar.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'No-Bake Chocolate Raspberry Cheesecake', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '403-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-12-10 22:21:53', '2015-12-10 22:21:53', '', 403, 'http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/?p=591', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(410, 1, '2015-11-30 17:07:17', '2015-11-30 17:07:17', '<p style="text-align: center;">Hooray! Its the most wonderful time of year and we are shouting from the rooftops, because we can finally put up our trees, hang up our wreaths and sing Christmas songs shamelessly!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">We hope your Thanksgiving was wonderful, however we are also excited to get on with this wonderful holiday, Christmas of course!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">We know if you clicked on this post you are just as excited as we are so lets celebrate together!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">What better way to make this holiday merry than making your home smell like Christmas?</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">We have the absolute GREATEST recipe for Fresh Homemade Holiday Potpourri. Just put your favorite fresh ingredients together in a pot and keep it simmering all day long!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">The best part is, you can really use whatever you have on hand.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">The must-haves in our opinion are cinnamon, citrus, ginger and vanilla. Nothing makes it feel more like the holidays than those wonderful scents. So good.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Enjoy!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Homemade-Holidays-Lets-Make-the-House-Smell-Like-Christmas-511.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-412 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Homemade-Holidays-Lets-Make-the-House-Smell-Like-Christmas-511.jpg" alt="Homemade-Holidays-Lets-Make-the-House-Smell-Like-Christmas-51" width="600" height="900" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Homemade-Holidays-Lets-Make-the-House-Smell-Like-Christmas-212.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-411 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Homemade-Holidays-Lets-Make-the-House-Smell-Like-Christmas-212.jpg" alt="Homemade-Holidays-Lets-Make-the-House-Smell-Like-Christmas-21" width="600" height="900" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Homemade-Holidays-Lets-Make-the-House-Smell-Like-Christmas-411.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-413 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Homemade-Holidays-Lets-Make-the-House-Smell-Like-Christmas-411.jpg" alt="Homemade-Holidays-Lets-Make-the-House-Smell-Like-Christmas-41" width="600" height="900" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 1/2 cups fresh cranberries</li>\r\n	<li>3 tangerines, halved</li>\r\n	<li>3 whole cinnamon sticks</li>\r\n	<li>2 star anise (optional) gives a strong black licorice smell.</li>\r\n	<li>1 teaspoon whole cloves</li>\r\n	<li>1 inch piece fresh ginger</li>\r\n	<li>1 vanilla bean + 1 tablespoon vanilla extract</li>\r\n	<li>1 small branch fresh pine</li>\r\n	<li>1 cup apple cider, pomegranate or cranberry juice</li>\r\n	<li>water</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>Instructions</h3>\r\nCombine all the ingredients in a medium size sauce pot. Fill the pot with water until it reaches 3/4 the way full. Place the pot on the stove and bring to a gentle boil. Reduce the heat to a simmer, adding more water as needed. I let mine simmer for close to 4 hours and then let it cool over night and simmer again the next day. Just be sure to keep adding more water.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Make Your Home Smell Like Christmas', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'make-your-home-smell-like-christmas', '', '', '2015-12-10 22:22:25', '2015-12-10 22:22:25', '', 0, 'http://directrangehoods.com/blog/?p=410', 0, 'post', '', 0),
