e-Holidays-Lets-Make-the-House-Smell-Like-Christmas-212.jpg" alt="Homemade-Holidays-Lets-Make-the-House-Smell-Like-Christmas-21" width="600" height="900" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Homemade-Holidays-Lets-Make-the-House-Smell-Like-Christmas-411.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-413 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Homemade-Holidays-Lets-Make-the-House-Smell-Like-Christmas-411.jpg" alt="Homemade-Holidays-Lets-Make-the-House-Smell-Like-Christmas-41" width="600" height="900" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 1/2 cups fresh cranberries</li>\r\n	<li>3 tangerines, halved</li>\r\n	<li>3 whole cinnamon sticks</li>\r\n	<li>2 star anise (optional) gives a strong black licorice smell.</li>\r\n	<li>1 teaspoon whole cloves</li>\r\n	<li>1 inch piece fresh ginger</li>\r\n	<li>1 vanilla bean + 1 tablespoon vanilla extract</li>\r\n	<li>1 small branch fresh pine</li>\r\n	<li>1 cup apple cider, pomegranate or cranberry juice</li>\r\n	<li>water</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>Instructions</h3>\r\nCombine all the ingredients in a medium size sauce pot. Fill the pot with water until it reaches 3/4 the way full. Place the pot on the stove and bring to a gentle boil. Reduce the heat to a simmer, adding more water as needed. I let mine simmer for close to 4 hours and then let it cool over night and simmer again the next day. Just be sure to keep adding more water.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Make Your Home Smell Like Christmas', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '410-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-12-10 22:22:25', '2015-12-10 22:22:25', '', 410, 'http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/?p=592', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(593, 1, '2015-12-10 22:23:01', '2015-12-10 22:23:01', '<p style="text-align: center;">There is something so simple and elegant about open shelving as it makes displaying your favorite dishes and accessories so much more fun. The real question is, does it really work? We think so! Not only does it keep the look of your kitchen open and airy but it draws your eyes upward and creates a unique interest in your kitchen. You would be surprised to know that even a grouping of the most mundane of items can look gorgeous. Take a look at 15 of our Favorite Open Shelving Ideas, and let us know what you think in the comments box below. Happy Monday!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/706fccc2e09045f02811900a420893ac1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-352 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/706fccc2e09045f02811900a420893ac1.jpg" alt="706fccc2e09045f02811900a420893ac" width="476" height="713" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.popsugar.com/home/Best-Kitchen-DIYs-35908426" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">Found on popsugar.com</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/2884b154caea4916af49419b93a35ea41.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-353 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/2884b154caea4916af49419b93a35ea41.jpg" alt="2884b154caea4916af49419b93a35ea4" width="646" height="968" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://decoholic.org/2015/06/23/kitchen-open-shelves/" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">Found on decoholic.org</a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/a1358e37d80030476822618b435892ea1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-354 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/a1358e37d80030476822618b435892ea1