(41, 1, '2015-08-03 20:38:34', '2015-08-03 20:38:34', 'Are you a person that loves to entertain? Have you been trying to think of a fun excuse to get your friends and family over to celebrate, and you just refuse to wait until Thanksgiving, Christmas, or Hanukkah to be that next special occasion?\n\nWell, it’s Summertime, your flowers are in bloom, your yard is looking great, and there is NO better time to host your very own Backyard Movie Night than RIGHT NOW. So what are you waiting for? We have searched to find our very favorite tips and tricks to make sure that you are prepared to throw the Best BackYard Movie Night of the Summer. Do we smell Popcorn?\n\n<!--more-->\n\n1)The first thing you will need to figure out is a <strong>movie screen</strong>. Here are some options:\n\n<strong>-Side of the House</strong>. This is definitely the easiest way to go, and if you have a white house even better! No set up or take down necessary!\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-43 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-Shot-2015-08-03-at-12.43.55-PM1.jpg" alt="Screen Shot 2015-08-03 at 12.43.55 PM" width="796" height="534" />\n<p style="text-align: center;">(Photo Credit: <strong>Mad Decorating</strong>)</p>\n<strong>-A Large White Sheet. </strong>This is definitely the most common set up for backyard movie nights. Not only is it super affordable, but you will find that the picture quality will turn out great.  If it still looks too transparent, double up your sheets for a more clear picture. Also, make sure you lay the sheet on a flat surface for the best outcome.\n\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-42 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Screen-Shot-2015-08-03-at-12.44.09-PM1.jpg" alt="Screen Shot 2015-08-03 at 12.44.09 PM" width="777" height="518" />\n<p style="text-align: center;">(Credit: <a href="http://www.thesitsgirls.com/diy/how-to-host-a-backyard-movie-night/?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed:+thesitsgirls/dIsr+(The+SITS+Girls)" target="_blank">TheSITSGirls.com</a>)</p>\n<strong>-Use Wood, Trees or PVC Pipes.</strong>\n\nIf you do not have a flat surface that will work, you can also use rope or cord and tie the sheet tightly to two trees, two pieces of wood, or make your own set up easily using PVC pipe to take the wrinkles right out, giving you the best results.\n\n<a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/41.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-44 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/41.jpg" alt="4" width="808" height="606" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n<p style="text-align: center;">(Credit: <a href="http://archive.wired.com/geekdad/2009/05/lights-cameras-insect-repellent-how-to-build-your-own-outdoor-movie-theater/" target="_blank">Dave Banks </a>)</p>\n2)<strong>Hanging Lights</strong>\n\nWhat is a movie theater with out mood lighting? Well, boring.. So help your guests get excited by working that lighting.\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/outdoor_movie_021.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-47 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/outdoor_movie_021.jpg" alt="outdoor_movie_02" width="800" height="546" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">(Image Credit: <a href="http://www.potterybarn.com/design-studio/articles/backyard-movie-screen.html" target="_blank">Potterybarn</a>)</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">3) <strong>Comfortable Seating</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">There is nothing worse than being uncomfortable while sitting through a two hour movie. Adding comfortable seating is not only important in order to keep your guests happy, but also a fun way to enhance the look and feel of your backyard bash by adding some colorful throw pillows and blankets in the mix.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>-DIY Seating-</strong> Who said that you need to spend a lot of money on expensive seating? Not us. Click on the credit link below to learn how to make these DIY backyard loungers.</p>\n<a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/backyard-theater1.jpg"><img class="wp-image-48 size-full aligncenter" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/backyard-theater1.jpg" alt="backyard-theater" width="600" height="834" /></a>\n<p style="text-align: center;">(Credit: <a href="http://www.notjustahousewife.net/2014/07/outdoor-movie-theater-seats.html" target="_blank">Not Just a Housewife</a>)</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">If this looks like too much work, you can:</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">-Sew pillows together to make comfy padding for your guests to lay on.<a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/tumblr_m5hhgoVHrJ1rvyz5qo5_r1_400_large1.jpg">\n</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/enhanced-24050-1393869412-91.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-52 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/enhanced-24050-1393869412-91.jpg" alt="enhanced-24050-1393869412-9" width="677" height="452" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">(Credit: <a href="http://www.buzzfeed.com/peggy/easy-backyard-diys?sub=2496210_2546793#.aar3pYJve2" target="_blank">BuzzFeed</a>)</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">-Use air mattresses</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/movie-night-backyard1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-53 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/movie-night-backyard1.jpg" alt="movie-night-backyard" width="585" height="878" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">(Credit: <a href="http://www.prettyprovidence.com/backyard-movie-night/" target="_blank">Pretty Providence</a>)</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">-Patio Furniture</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/21.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-50 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/21.jpg" alt="2" width="653" height="527" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">(Photo Credit: <a href="http://www.thegardenglove.com/15-easy-diy-projects-to-make-your-backyard-awesome/" target="_blank">The Garden Glove</a>)</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">-Sheets, Blankets, and LOTS of pillows.<img class="aligncenter wp-image-49 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/tumblr_m5hhgoVHrJ1rvyz5qo5_r1_400_large1.jpg" alt="tumblr_m5hhgoVHrJ1rvyz5qo5_r1_400_large" width="648" height="716" /></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">(Credit: <a href="http://www.kikareichert.com.br/inspirations/2011/07/cinema-ao-ar-livre/?utm_source=feedburner&amp;utm_medium=feed&amp;utm_campaign=Feed:+KikaReichert+(Kika+Reichert)&amp;utm_content=Google+Reader" target="_blank">Kiki Reichert</a>)</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">-Inflatable furniture</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/spin_prod_7485161121.jpeg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-51 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/spin_prod_7485161121.jpeg" alt="spin_prod_748516112" width="669" height="669" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">(Credit: <a href="http://www.kmart.com/intex-pull-out-sofa/p-089W004736967001P" target="_blank">Kmart</a>)</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">3)<strong>Popcorn Bar </strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">You got that right, popcorn mixed with gummy bears, m&amp;m''s, and whatever else you so desire.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/DIY-Movie-Night-Popcorn-Bar-FamilyFreshMeals.com-Fun-for-the-whole-family1.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-54 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/DIY-Movie-Night-Popcorn-Bar-FamilyFreshMeals.com-Fun-for-the-whole-family1.png" alt="DIY-Movie-Night-Popcorn-Bar-FamilyFreshMeals.com-Fun-for-the-whole-family" width="725" height="483" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">(Credit: http: <a href="http://www.familyfreshmeals.com/2014/07/diy-movie-night-popcorn-bar.html" target="_blank">Family Fresh Meals</a>)</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">4) <strong>Light Beverages </strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">You could throw some cans of assorted pop in a cooler, but remember it''s all about the details. We say take the route that''s more fun, and find soda in glass bottles. To top it off, tie a straw around each bottle with some twine. Your guests will appreciate that little extra effort.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/70cca627ca4b10306454d1431b0ba3fa1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-55 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/70cca627ca4b10306454d1431b0ba3fa1.jpg" alt="70cca627ca4b10306454d1431b0ba3fa" width="570" height="380" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">(Credit: <a href="https://www.etsy.com/listing/73126699/300-custom-wedding-soda-bottle-wrappers?utm_source=Pinterest&amp;utm_medium=PageTools&amp;utm_campaign=Share" target="_blank">Etsy</a>)</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Well there you have it! We hope your outdoor movie night is a major hit! Let us know which idea is your favorite and any other tips you may have in the comments box below!</p>\n&nbsp;', 'How to Throw the Best Backyard Movie Night Of The Summer', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-to-throw-the-best-backyard-movie-night-of-the-summer', '', '', '2015-08-03 20:38:34', '2015-08-03 20:38:34', '', 0, 'http://directrangehoods.com/blog/?p=41', 0, 'post', '', 0),
