(369, 1, '2015-10-27 18:09:23', '2015-10-27 18:09:23', '<div class="ERSIngredients"></div>\n<div class="ERSIngredientsHeader ERSHeading"></div>\n<div class="ERSIngredientsHeader ERSHeading"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/chipotle-pizza-121.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-371 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/chipotle-pizza-121.jpg" alt="chipotle-pizza-12" width="550" height="825" /></a></div>\n<div class="ERSIngredientsHeader ERSHeading"></div>\n<div class="ERSIngredientsHeader ERSHeading"></div>\n<div class="ERSIngredientsHeader ERSHeading"></div>\n<div class="ERSIngredientsHeader ERSHeading" style="text-align: center;">Talk out Delicious! This Double Loaded Chipotle Chicken Pizza is topped with delicious chipotle salsa as the sauce, chunks of fresh chicken, red onion, and Mexican cheese. Once the pizza is baked it is topped with a black bean-corn salsa, a lime cream sauce, and fresh cilantro for even more mouth bursting flavor. Give it a try, you will not regret it! Enjoy!</div>\n<div class="ERSIngredients">\n<div class="ERSIngredientsHeader ERSHeading"><strong>Ingredients</strong></div>\n<ul>\n	<li class="ingredient">1 cup mild thick and chunky salsa</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">2 chipotle peppers in adobo sauce, minced</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">1½ cups diced, cooked chicken</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">¼ cup thinly sliced red onion</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">1 cup shredded Mexican cheese</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">1 pound pizza dough</li>\n</ul>\n<div class="ERSSectionHead"><strong>Black Bean-Corn Salsa</strong></div>\n<ul>\n	<li class="ingredient">¾ cup canned black beans, rinsed and drained</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">¾ cup canned or frozen corn</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">¼ cup finely chopped red onion</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">½ tablespoon olive oil</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">2 tablespoons salsa</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">¼ teaspoon ground cumin</li>\n</ul>\n<div class="ERSSectionHead"><strong>Cilantro Lime Cream</strong></div>\n<ul>\n	<li class="ingredient">⅓ cup sour cream</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">1 tablespoon lime juice</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">2 tablespoons finely chopped, fresh cilantro</li>\n</ul>\n<div class="swoop-container nolinks" data-width="660">\n<div class="spx-button-bubble" data-purpose="lp">\n<div class="spx-bb-box">\n<div class="spx-bb-item spx-bb-cta"><strong>Instructions</strong></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="ERSInstructions">\n<ol>\n	<li class="instruction">Bring pizza dough to room temperature for 90 minutes.</li>\n	<li class="instruction">You want to heat the oven, with a pizza stone inside, for at least 30 minutes before using it. Oven should be heated to at least 450 degrees. Preferably 500 if your oven will go that high. Use the middle rack for the pizza stone.</li>\n	<li class="instruction">Make the Black Bean-Corn Salsa. Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl and refrigerate until needed.</li>\n	<li class="instruction">Make Cilantro Lime Cream. Combine ingredients in a small bowl and refrigerate.</li>\n	<li class="instruction">Divide dough into 2 pieces. Working with one piece at a time, stretch or roll the dough into approximately a 12 inch round. I shape it with my hands without it touching any surface, but if you are using a surface, lightly flour it.</li>\n	<li class="instruction">Lightly dust a pizza peel or back of a cookie sheet with cornmeal or flour. Place shaped dough on top. You want to make sure there is enough cornmeal or flour to keep the dough from sticking to the peel or it will get misshapen when you transfer it to the pizza stone.</li>\n	<li class="instruction">Stir together the 1 cup of salsa and the chipotle peppers and spread about ⅓ to ½ a cup on the dough. Top with half the cheese, chicken, and red onion.</li>\n	<li class="instruction">Transfer to pizza stone by tilting and shaking the pizza peel until it slides all the way onto the stone. Bake for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and crust is golden.</li>\n	<li class="instruction">To serve, top with black bean-corn salsa and drizzle with lime cream sauce. (I used a plastic bag and snipped the corner to drizzle the cream sauce. This only works well if you have very finely chopped the cilantro.</li>\n	<li class="instruction">Repeat to make one more pizza.</li>\n</ol>\n</div>', 'Double Loaded Chipotle Chicken Pizza', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'double-loaded-chipotle-chicken-pizza', '', '', '2015-10-27 18:09:23', '2015-10-27 18:09:23', '', 0, 'http://directrangehoods.com/blog/?p=369', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(381, 1, '2015-11-03 22:22:38', '2015-11-03 22:22:38', '<div class="ERSIngredients">\n<p style="text-align: center;">This is not just your ordinary Garlic Bread.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">We are convinced that this delicious Cheese Garlic Pull Apart Bread recipe will leave you wanting MORE and MORE.  Enjoy!</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Don''t forget to subscribe for more fresh recipes!</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/DSC_02972.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-382 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/DSC_02972.jpg" alt="DSC_0297" width="680" height="1024" /></a></p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong><em>INGREDIENTS</em></strong>\n<ul>\n	<li class="ingredient">1 crusty loaf, preferably sourdough or Vienna</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">¾ cup shredded Mozzarella cheese (or other melting cheese)</li>\n</ul>\n<div class="ERSSectionHead"><em><strong>GARLIC BUTTER</strong></em></div>\n<ul>\n	<li class="ingredient">100g/3.5oz unsalted butter, softened</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">2 garlic cloves, minced</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">⅜ tsp salt</li>\n	<li class="ingredient">1 tbsp fresh parsley, finely chopped</li>\n</ul>\n<div class="ERSClear"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="ERSInstructions">\n<div class="ERSInstructionsHeader ERSHeading"><strong>INSTRUCTIONS</strong></div>\n<ol>\n	<li class="instruction">Preheat the oven to 180C/350F.</li>\n	<li class="instruction">Melt butter and then mix in other Garlic Butter ingredients.</li>\n	<li class="instruction">Cut the bread on a diagonal into 2cm/1" diamonds but do not cut all the way through the bread (just like you would cut a french stick for garlic bread).</li>\n	<li class="instruction">Use your fingers or a knife to pry open each crack and drizzle in a teaspoon of butter and stuff in a pinch of cheese. This might sound like a bit of an effort, but I promise you it is worth it! You don''t need to be super neat, it''s nice to have some of the butter drizzled over the crust.</li>\n	<li class="instruction">Wrap with foil and bake for 15minutes until the cheese has mostly melted, then unwrap and bake for 5 minutes more to make the bread nice and crusty.</li>\n	<li class="instruction">Serve immediately.</li>\n</ol>\n<div class="ERSClear"></div>\n</div>\n<div class="ERSNotesDiv">\n<div class="ERSNotesHeader"><strong>NOTE:</strong></div>\n<ul>\n	<li class="ERSNotesHeader">The denser the bread, the better the pieces will hold together when pulled off.</li>\n	<li class="ERSNotesHeader">Use already baked bread, not uncooked bread dough.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>', 'Cheese Garlic Pull Apart Bread', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cheese-garlic-pull-apart-bread', '', '', '2015-11-03 22:22:38', '2015-11-03 22:22:38', '', 0, 'http://directrangehoods.com/blog/?p=381', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(386, 1, '2015-11-05 22:49:03', '2015-11-05 22:49:03', '<p style="text-align: center;">It''s that time of year when we are starting to make our checklists to get ready for the BIGGEST day in November.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">When all of your relatives from every corner of the universe come together to mingle and eat a giant turkey. That time to celebrate the wonderful spirited occasion we all know and love, <strong>THANKSGIVING.</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">We have come up with a game plan to help  you <strong>DOMINATE</strong> this holiday and do it with class.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">We know planning a big event can feel a bit intimidating, but if you plan ahead it can actually even be fun!</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Your guests will be wondering how you did it, and after you can put your feet up and smile knowing that you put together a great event, and you did it WELL.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>1) Break It Down </strong>- with a checklist. When a fabulous idea comes to your mind quickly write it down. That creative inspiration you need to run with! Write down how many guests will be attending, what decorations you are planning on setting out, what food you are planning to make, and anything else that you feel is important to not forget. <strong>Fun Note-</strong> Did you know every time a box is checked on a to-d0 list you get endorphins? How cool is that?</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/devon-inventories-exeter-11.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-389 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/devon-inventories-exeter-11.jpg" alt="devon-inventories-exeter-1" width="647" height="492" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>2) Meal Planning </strong>- One thing that can kill a good Thanksgiving, is a poorly made turkey and poorly made food. As much as we would like to believe that our families come travel all of the way from across town to share special memories and bonding time, we are almost more convinced its about THE FOOD. Make good food this Thanksgiving, and your guests just might come to see you again next year. Use this time to look up delicious recipes, check out recipe ratings and reviews on good turkey, and don''t forget about the appetizers and dessert! If you know that cooking is not your strongest strength.. maybe use these next few weeks to practice some recipes, or if you really doubt your abilities its never a bad idea to assign the turkey to someone else.. Just Saying.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/f370d6efec5df58aecda471a91a949d21.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-390 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/f370d6efec5df58aecda471a91a949d21.jpg" alt="f370d6efec5df58aecda471a91a949d2" width="671" height="671" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.bhg.com/thanksgiving/recipes/traditional-menu/" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">bhg.com</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><b>3) Start Decorating</b> - Just think, what decorations will make your Home feel cozy and warm? Pull out the warm blankets and faux fur throws, fall wreaths, leaf garlands, and pumpkin scented candles. Dress up your front porch and your your fireplace mantle, display your favorite fall dishes, and your favorite fall quotes, display your favorite books on your coffee table. If you feel like going the extra mile, switch out your couch pillows and some wall art.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/a214a9d1ba094e673e9aa1ab37f7e6541.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-391 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/a214a9d1ba094e673e9aa1ab37f7e6541.jpg" alt="a214a9d1ba094e673e9aa1ab37f7e654" width="600" height="745" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.bystephanielynn.com/2011/09/10-tips-for-purchasing-caring-for-fall-mums-my-tuesday-ten-no-14.html" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">Found on bystephanielynn.com</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/47b0f70627619718bc964af5ba18caca1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-392 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/47b0f70627619718bc964af5ba18caca1.jpg" alt="47b0f70627619718bc964af5ba18caca" width="652" height="909" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://thefrugalhomemaker.com/2013/10/01/31-days-fall-inspiration-fall-mantel/" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">Found on thefrugalhomemaker.com</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/3ffe22fffbf9cc8812936b153dc629992.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-242 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/3ffe22fffbf9cc8812936b153dc629992.jpg" alt="3ffe22fffbf9cc8812936b153dc62999" width="600" height="900" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://lilacsandlonghorns.blogspot.com/2012/09/five-simple-fall-decorating-ideas.html" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">Found on lilacsandlonghorns.blogspot.com</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>4) Table Setting </strong>- The food should be delicious, but how will it be presented? A good party is all about good presentation! Want to make your guests feel like they walked into a cozy palace? Let these table displays inspire you! The table is your canvas, now create art!</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/ab9abf88d862f9c53a1ac05df59840822.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-393 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/ab9abf88d862f9c53a1ac05df59840822.jpg" alt="ab9abf88d862f9c53a1ac05df5984082" width="600" height="956" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.lizmarieblog.com/2013/11/beautiful-thanksgiving-table-idea/?crlt.pid=camp.xn4mfhVmpDLd&amp;crlt.pid=camp.42XC6XcoRuXv" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">Found on lizmarieblog.com</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/7f2cb0967942333fb9075b9db44c206f1.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-394 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/7f2cb0967942333fb9075b9db44c206f1.jpg" alt="7f2cb0967942333fb9075b9db44c206f" width="600" height="898" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://cdn.homedit.com/30-thanksgiving-table-setting-ideas-for-a-festive-decor-celebration/" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">Found on cdn.homedit.com</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/e013516bef5bf117024e131875783fc01.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-395 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/e013516bef5bf117024e131875783fc01.jpg" alt="e013516bef5bf117024e131875783fc0" width="550" height="824" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.decoratingyoursmallspace.com/not-your-mothers-thanksgiving-table/" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">Found on decoratingyoursmallspace.com</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/2c17d6c8800667146dde39223c1e30b01.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-396 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/2c17d6c8800667146dde39223c1e30b01.jpg" alt="2c17d6c8800667146dde39223c1e30b0" width="554" height="832" /></a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.lizmarieblog.com/2013/11/beautiful-thanksgiving-table-idea/?crlt.pid=camp.xn4mfhVmpDLd&amp;crlt.pid=camp.4Ndq161z5XpZ" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">Found on lizmarieblog.com</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>5) Invites </strong>- Invites set the tone for the whole event and give your guests something to be excited about! Are you wanting a more casual Thanksgiving? Then keep it simple and send out an email invite or order some invites online through an invitation service. Or, you can choose the fancy route, and design some custom invitations in a beautiful, bow wrapped package that will make your guests says OOH-LA-LA!</p>\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-397 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/1179523e09b98ffc71cab5061369458f1.jpg" alt="1179523e09b98ffc71cab5061369458f" width="548" height="429" />\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.countryliving.com/cooking/entertaining/fall-party-ideas#slide-1" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">Found on countryliving.com</a></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>6) Activities </strong>- Life is busy, and it''s not everyday that your whole family gets together, so why not make some real memories and have some fun? The best thing to do before dessert is play some fun games where everyone can join in and have some fun! If you have a competitive family, any game that involves a team is always a good idea.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>7) Take Home Gift - </strong>If you haven''t figured it out, the best way to keep the leftovers at your house is send each guest with a festive take home gift! Whether you decide that will be a sweet note with a bottle of apple cider, or a box of chocolate''s! We think its perfectly okay to think that you deserve to keep the leftovers, after all, you were the one to put this event together, and made most of the food. Although, it is ThanksGIVING, so if you feel like giving away your extras, I''m sure it will make someones day. Even though we are convince that Turkey Roll Sandwiches and Pumpkin Pie almost taste even better the second day.</p>\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-398 size-full" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/edac54049f6e46698bd653c0b1547e9c1.jpg" alt="edac54049f6e46698bd653c0b1547e9c" width="700" height="1050" />\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.bloglovin.com/blog/post/7867181/3731829515" rel="nofollow" data-element-type="27">Found on bloglovin.com</a> By Bright and Bold</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;">Hopefully you feel a little more prepared on how to get ready for Thanksgiving. Let us know what you do to get ready for Thanksgiving in the comments box below!</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Happy FALLidays!</strong></p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong> </strong></p>', 'Plan Ahead: How to Get Ready For Thanksgiving', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'plan-ahead-how-to-get-ready-for-thanksgiving', '', '', '2015-11-05 22:49:03', '2015-11-05 22:49:03', '', 0, 'http://directrangehoods.com/blog/?p=386', 0, 'post', '', 0),
