(403, 1, '2015-11-13 16:35:19', '2015-11-13 16:35:19', '<p style="text-align: center;">It''s that wonderful, magical time of year, Wishing you happiness, joy, and cheer.\r\nMay all your days be warm and bright,\r\nAnd your nights enhanced by holiday light.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Enjoy your delectable holiday foods,\r\nAs parties and gifts create holiday moods.\r\nFavorite people play a meaningful part,\r\nWhile treasured rituals warm your heart.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Just when you thought this dish couldn''t look any more delicious, this Holiday Dessert</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">not only has a TO DIE FOR lemony cream filling and fresh berries, but it''s also Gluten-free!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">This is one Holiday Dessert that is a guaranteed winner!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Enjoy this No-Bake Chocolate Raspberry Cheesecake delight.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">May it fill your bellies and taste just right.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Dig in! </strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Raspberry-Chocolate-Cheesecake.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-404 " src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Raspberry-Chocolate-Cheesecake.jpg" alt="37385_l" width="851" height="612" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Ingredients </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="ingredient-table" style="text-align: left;">\r\n	<li> <label for="ingredient-0-0">2 x 160g pkt Macro Gluten-free Double Chocolate Biscuits</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-1">80g butter, melted, cooled</label> <label for="ingredient-0-2">375g cream cheese, at room temperature</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-3">125ml (1/2 cup) thickened cream</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-4">70g (1/3 cup) caster sugar</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-5">1 lemon, rind finely grated</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-6">1 tbs gelatine powder</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-7">60ml (1/4 cup) boiling water</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-8">300g fresh raspberries</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-9">60g dark chocolate melts, melted</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-10">Fresh baby mint sprigs, to serve</label></li>\r\n	<li><label for="ingredient-0-11">Pure icing sugar, to dust</label></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Directions</strong>\r\n<div class="module-content">\r\n<div class="content-item tab-content current method-tab-content">\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li class="methods" style="text-align: left;">\r\n<p class="description">Process biscuits and butter in a food processor until well combined. Press over the base and sides of a 2.5cm-deep, 13 x 36cm rectangular fluted tart tin with removable base. Freeze for 15 minutes or until firm.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li class="methods" style="text-align: left;">\r\n<p class="description">Use electric beaters to beat cream cheese, cream, sugar and lemon rind until well combined and sugar has dissolved. In a small jug, sprinkle gelatine over boiling water and whisk until dissolved. Add to cheese mixture and beat until smooth.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li class="methods" style="text-align: left;">\r\n<p class="description">Fold through 200g raspberries. Spoon into tin. Chill in fridge for 4 hours or until set.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li class="methods" style="text-align: left;">\r\n<p class="description">Meanwhile, line a tray with baking paper. Dip the tips of remaining raspberries into chocolate and place on tray to set.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li class="methods" style="text-align: left;">\r\n<p class="description">Top the cheesecake with chocolate raspberries and mint. Dust with icing sugar.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'No-Bake Chocolate Raspberry Cheesecake', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'no-bake-chocolate-raspberry-cheesecake', '', '', '2015-12-10 22:21:53', '2015-12-10 22:21:53', '', 0, 'http://directrangehoods.com/blog/?p=403', 0, 'post', '', 0),
