"padding-left: 60px;">While this might mean a group of people following someone important, remember that by improving your life you are as important as they come. We all should look up to someone who is constantly trying to improve their lives. By having a support crew we become accountable and have someone to keep us focused.</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>8.  Get started!</strong></p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 60px;">Talking about a goal is good, planning for it is awesome, but the most important step you can take is to take a step. It might seem hard and results so far away, but you will never get there by talking or wishing. Put one foot in front of the other and step by step your goal will get closer and closer.</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 60px;"></p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">What are some of your goals for this new year? Diet? Graduate? Learn something new?</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">If one of your new year''s resolution is to remodel your home, check out how a range hood adds so much to a home:</p>', '8 Tips for Staying Motivated and Sticking to Your Goals', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '650-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-12-29 22:55:22', '2015-12-29 22:55:22', '', 650, 'http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/650-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(655, 5, '2015-12-29 23:03:49', '2015-12-29 23:03:49', '<a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/GGQX7WXAAC.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-651"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-651 size-large" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/GGQX7WXAAC-1024x683.jpg" alt="A Man who has achieved his goal of reaching the top of a mountain" width="1024" height="683" /></a>\r\n\r\nIt''s the end of the year, and that means new year''s resolutions. You know, that time when the gym will be packed for about a month, the salad portion of the superstore will be barren and people telling themselves: this is the year! Well, we love your enthusiasm, but here are the facts: 62% of Americans make New Year''s Resolutions each year, people who set goals are 10 times more likely to achieve those goals (good on you if you did!), and unfortunately only about 8% of people are successful in reaching those goals. So how can we set goals and have a higher success rate? Well, here are some tips for getting and staying motivated about your goals this new year, it can work for diets, exercise or any other type of goal.\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">8 Tips for Success With Your Goals</h2>\r\n<p style="text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;"><strong>1. Change your mindset!</strong></p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 60px;">Number one for a reason, this step is fundamental for any goal you set in life. Remember, you are setting a goal to change your life, not just to lose weight or exercise. This mindset will help you find a deeper reason in what you are doing and ultimately make you more passionate about the goal you set.</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>2. Set small and large goals (short term &amp; long term)</strong></p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 60px;">This step serves two purposes, because these smaller goals should keep you on track to having success with your larger goals, and so that every time you have a success no matter how small you are more encouraged and hyped to keep going. If you only set a large goal you will become discouraged very quickly, but by taking it step by step you will constantly keep progressing.</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>3. Track your success</strong></p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 60px;">You set a goal and halfway through you try to remember where you started and have no clue how far you have gotten. By keeping a record of your success you motivate yourself and know where you stand. Keep a positive outlook on this as you go and use your current status as motivation to keep pushing forward! Every pound, step, or action is a success, treat them as such.</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>4. Admit to yourself that you are not perfect</strong></p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 60px;">the more my mother said I was perfect, the more I kept finding out I am far from that! Reaching our goals does not mean we did it without any hiccups. There will be times when we are weak, and this is normal. By admitting this to ourselves, we can remember that messing up does not mean giving up.</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>5. Expect setbacks</strong></p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 60px;">They will happen but when they do, don''t be discouraged. The danger with setbacks or messing up, is that when we mess up a little we think there is no going back and might as well mess up a lot. "I ate a cookie so I might as well eat the rest". A little mistake does not mean you cannot come back!</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>6. Reward yourself</strong></p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 60px;">Remember those successes we talked about? They should be rewarded, and serve as a motivation for the next little success until you''ve completed your goal. In dieting, some decide to have a "cheat" day, a day in which you can have all the treats you pushed away for the week.</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>7. Have an entourage</strong></p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 60px;">While this might mean a group of people following someone important, remember that by improving your life you are as important as they come. We all should look up to someone who is constantly trying to improve their lives. By having a support crew we become accountable and have someone to keep us focused.</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;"><strong>8.  Get started!</strong></p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 60px;">Talking about a goal is good, planning for it is awesome, but the most important step you can take is to take a step. It might seem hard and results so far away, but you will never get there by talking or wishing. Put one foot in front of the other and step by step your goal will get closer and closer.</p>\r\n<p style="padding-left: 30px;">What are some of your goals for this new year? Diet? Graduate? Learn something new? What have been some of the hardest parts of completing a goal? Tell us in the comments below!</p>', '8 Tips for Staying Motivated and Sticking to Your Goals', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '650-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-12-29 23:03:49', '2015-12-29 23:03:49', '', 650, 'http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/650-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
