(668, 1, '2016-01-06 21:31:15', '2016-01-06 21:31:15', '<p style="text-align: center;">There is just something special about Pasta made from scratch.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Make Fresh Homemade Pasta by Hand following these Easy Steps and using only three ingredients!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Let us know what Pasta you plan on making in the comments box below!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Subscribe to join the fun and be up to date with the best recipes, Kitchen Design Tips,  Entertaining Ideas and More!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Enjoy!</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Hand-Made-Pasta.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-669"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-669" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/I4MIIMHZ5M-1-1024x683.jpg" alt="Make Fresh Homemade Pasta By Hand" width="882" height="583" /></a></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Ingredients</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">2 1/2 cups flour, plus extra for dusting</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">4 eggs</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">2 Tsp. extra-virgin olive oil</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Makes:</strong> About 1 pound</p>\r\n<strong>Directions:</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Add 2 cups of flour on a clean surface making a small gap/hole shape in the flour.</li>\r\n	<li>Crack the eggs into a large measuring cup. Add the oil to the measuring cup and then pour egg-oil mixture into the center of the well shape that you made.</li>\r\n	<li>Whisk the eggs in the well, without drawing in any flour, until they are mixed well together.</li>\r\n	<li>Add in the flour. Use a fork to slowly draw the flour into the center and  and stir in the flour and egg-oil mixture together. Mix together until you have a shaggy mess of dough.</li>\r\n	<li>Knead dough ingredients together. Make sure you are using a clean work surface and then dust the surface with flour. Transfer the dough into the floured surface by kneading it together, pushing down and away from you, turning dough repeatedly until the dough feels nice and smooth. Knead for about 7-10 minutes. Sprinkle more flour in the mixture if the dough feels too sticky</li>\r\n	<li>Let the Dough Rest. Shape the Pasta Dough into a round ball. Cover the ball in an overturned bowl, or a bowl with a towel over it and let it rest for 30 minutes before rolling.</li>\r\n	<li>Roll out the Dough into thin layer and cut them into desired noodle shape. Use a Pasta Cutter if needed</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/1..png" rel="attachment wp-att-684"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-684" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/1.-724x1024.png" alt="Make Fresh Homemade Pasta By Hand" width="890" height="1223" /></a>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Now you have made yourself some delicious fresh homemade Pasta!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Cook the noodles and make a Classic Pasta Dish, or use the dough to make pasta shells and stuff them with all of your favorite fresh ingredients.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Bon Appétit!</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/9FN3KR6632.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-678"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-678" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/9FN3KR6632-1024x609.jpg" alt="Make Fresh Homemade Pasta By Hand" width="898" height="539" /></a></p>', 'Make Fresh Homemade Pasta By Hand', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'makefreshhomemadepastabyhand', '', '', '2016-01-06 21:35:29', '2016-01-06 21:35:29', '', 0, 'http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/?p=668', 0, 'post', '', 0),
