(753, 2, '2016-03-10 17:39:54', '2016-03-10 17:39:54', '<h1 style="text-align: center;"><em><strong>WHAT MAKES A KITCHEN UNIQUE?</strong></em></h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3 style="text-align: center;"><strong>What makes your kitchen unique? When it comes to picking the perfect design elements for a kitchen space </strong><strong>what is it that makes your own kitchen beautiful and different? </strong></h3>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;">We know that the trick to good design is all in the details, but we wanted to dig deeper, to find what is it EXACTLY that makes kitchens around the world beautiful.</h4>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;">So sit back, and relax, and take notes as we share our top secrets for dreamy kitchen spaces with you.</h4>\r\n<h4 style="text-align: center;">Who knows, maybe you will find a little kitchen inspiration to move you for your your next home project.</h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3> <strong>The Magic is in  The Appliances</strong></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you''ve had a friend or a family member that has told you that Kitchen Appliances don''t matter, please do yourself a favor and take a walk outside, turn on some hot and heavy politics debate, or do just about anything to keep yourself from listening a second longer. Why? Because the quality of your appliances in your kitchen should be the main foundation to build off of, your beautiful statement pieces, your powerful cooking machines, and will basically tell your guests if you cook like a chef, or whip up a five minute easy–mac and cheese every night. The respect is all in the appliances, and you better believe it. And if you think the Range Hood is the statement piece in the kitchen, we may be a little biased, but we couldn''t agree more. There is serious power in having a beautiful, top quality range hood to display in your dream kitchen, so make sure you invest in one that will last you for years to come.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_743" align="aligncenter" width="1151"]<a class="stainless_steel_range_hood_proline_range_hoods_" href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/stainless_steel_range_hood.jpg" target="_blank" rel="http://www.prolinerangehoods.com/index.php?main_page=product_info&amp;cPath=32_48&amp;products_id=345"><img class="stainless_steel_range_hood_proline_range_hoods_ wp-image-743" title="stainless_steel_range_hood_proline_range_hoods_" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/stainless_steel_range_hood.jpg" alt="kitchen unique stainless_steel_range_hood_unique_kitchen" width="1151" height="758" /></a> <a href="http://www.prolinerangehoods.com/index.php?main_page=product_info&amp;cPath=32_48&amp;products_id=345" target="_blank">Range Hood: Proline PLFW 750 Wall Mount Range Hood</a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_746" align="aligncenter" width="1147"]<a class="stainless_steel_range_hood_proline_range_hoods_PLFW_750" href="http://www.prolinerangehoods.com/index.php?main_page=product_info&amp;cPath=32_48&amp;products_id=333" rel="stainless_steel_range_hood_proline_range_hoods_PLFW_750"><img class="wp-image-746" title="stainless_steel_range_hoods_proline_range_hoods_PLFW_750" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/proline_range_hood.jpg" alt="kitchen unique stainless_steel_proline_range_hoods_PLFW_750" width="1147" height="756" /></a> <a href="http://stainless_steel_range_hood_proline_range_hoods" target="_blank">Range Hood: Proline PLFW 750</a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3> Its all about the <b>Details, Details, Details...</b></h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nHave you ever heard the quote:\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">"When it comes to design modesty is great,</h2>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">and quietness is nice, but letting your</h2>\r\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">imagination run free is always more fun." <span class="_58cl"><a class="_58cn" href="https://www.facebook.com/hashtag/kitcheninspiration?source=feed_text&amp;story_id=1049630345073624" data-ft="{&quot;tn&quot;:&quot;*N&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:104}">‪</a> </span></h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<span class="_58cl">Your kitchen should be your absolute favorite room in your home, not just a place to cook, but more so, a place where you feel free to be be yourself, create, and feel inspired. Why be so serious when it comes to design? Our advice, be original and make your kitchen feel like nobody but you could own it! These kitchens shown below are both beautiful, but we would rather hang out with the person who owns the kitchen on the bottom, wouldn''t you? We have to believe that a kitchen that is cheerful and full of life can say a lot about the person who owns it. Taking a kitchen from bland to grand is all in the details. No need to get too crazy and blow your money on the most custom and  intricate details, but you will be amazed with what elements you will be able to  find and find some amazing deals that are actually just as affordable. Here are some of our favorite stand out details to acknowledge when designing your own Kitchen:</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>The Floor:</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_749" align="aligncenter" width="1147"]<a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/kitchen_unique_kitchen_floor-1.png" rel="mediterranean_floor_tile_kitchen_unique_proline_kitchen_blog"><img class="wp-image-749" title="mediterranean_floor_tile_kitchen_unique_proline_kitchen_blog" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/kitchen_unique_kitchen_floor-1.png" alt="kitchen unique mediterranean_floor_tile_kitchen_unique_proline_kitchen_blog" width="1147" height="909" /></a> Beautiful Black and White Mediterranean Floor Tile, Such a Dream.[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>The Hardware:</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_751" align="aligncenter" width="1147"]<a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/kitchen_unique_kitchen_hardware_proline_kitchen_blog-1.png" rel="kitchen_unique_kitchen_hardware_proline_kitchen_blog"><img class="kitchen_unique_kitchen_hardware_proline_kitchen_blog wp-image-751 size-full" title="kitchen_unique_kitchen_hardware_proline_kitchen_blog" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/kitchen_unique_kitchen_hardware_proline_kitchen_blog-1.png" alt="kitchen unique_kitchen_hardware_proline_kitchen_blog" width="1147" height="1263" /></a> Finding Unique Kitchen Hardware is Everything.[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>The Lighting:</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_752" align="aligncenter" width="1147"]<a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/kitchen-unique-kitchen_lighting_proline_kitchen_blog.png" rel="kitchen unique kitchen_lighting_proline_kitchen_blog"><img class="kitchen unique kitchen_lighting_proline_kitchen_blog wp-image-752 size-full" title="kitchen unique kitchen_lighting_proline_kitchen_blog" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/kitchen-unique-kitchen_lighting_proline_kitchen_blog-e1457631060196.png" alt="kitchen unique kitchen_lighting_proline_kitchen_blog" width="1147" height="835" /></a> A dazzling pendant light is the focal point in this Unique Kitchen.[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n<h3> Give is some Personality.</h3>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMaking a kitchen unique is all about making it feel like its yours. Like somehow your personality', 'What Makes a Kitchen Unique?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '739-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-10 17:39:54', '2016-03-10 17:39:54', '', 739, 'http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/739-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(755, 5, '2016-03-16 20:45:47', '2016-03-16 20:45:47', '<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-771" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/pots-and-pans-1024x678.jpg" alt="pots and pans" width="1024" height="678" />\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to cooking, we know that the devil is in the details. Whether it is a few extra minutes in the oven or that extra dash of salt, a mouth-watering meal can easily become the meal your family jokes about for years to come. Did you know that your Cookware can also have an effect on your food? From the way it cooks yo ur food to reacting with it, learn about the different types of cookware you can use!\r\n&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Types of Cookware:</h2>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>Aluminum</h2>\r\n<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-759" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/aluminum-pan-300x169.jpg" alt="aluminum pan" width="300" height="169" />\r\nAluminum is one of the most inexpensive options of cookware available. It is an excellent conductor of heat making it a great choice for sautéing and frying foods. The drawback of aluminum is that it reacts to acidic and alkaline foods, causing it to corrode and affect the taste of the food being cooked. Aluminum pots and pans can be given a special coating to protect the metal from corrosion and make it stick-resistant, this is called anodized aluminum.\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<strong>TIP:</strong> Hard water tends to darken aluminum. To remove stains, use a cream of tarter and white vinegar combination.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h2>Stainless Steel</h2>\r\n<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-763" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Stainless-Steel-300x224.jpg" alt="Stainless Steel Cookware" width="300" height="224" />\r\nStainless Steel is great material to use because it keeps its bright shine and has good tensile strength, preventing it from denting easily. Stainless steel is a good material for any type of pan because it does not corrode and does not react with alkaline or acidic materials like many other materials. The problem with stainless steel is that it does not conduct heat well. To combat this problem, pots and pans made from stainless steel have should have a thick aluminum or copper core in the bottom of the pan to help conduct heat more evenly and make the pan more responsive to heat.\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<strong>TIP:</strong> Stainless steel cookware are dishwasher safe but the drying process can cause the water spots. To avoid water spots, remove the pan from the dishwasher before it is dry and wipe with a soft cloth.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h2>Copper</h2>\r\n<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-765" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/copper-pots-300x200.jpg" alt="copper cookware" width="300" height="200" />\r\nCopper conducts heat evenly and is very responsive to heat. It heats up quickly and will also cool down quickly when removed from the heat, preventing sautés and delicate foods from burning and becoming overdone. Because copper distributes heat so evenly and efficiently, it is the best choice for frying and sautéing, but it is also a good choice for many other cooking methods.\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<strong>TIP:</strong> Avoid using abrasive materials to clean. Use copper polish to keep copper from tarnishing and free from white spots. The interior should be re-tinned every couple of years, depending on usage.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h2>Cast Iron</h2>\r\n<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-769" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/cast-iron-pan-300x200.jpg" alt="cast iron pan" width="300" height="200" />\r\nCast Iron conducts heat evenly. It heats slowly but once it is hot it holds the heat well. This makes it good for deep frying and slow-cooking. It can be used on top of the stove and in the oven. Cast Iron is very susceptible to\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<strong>TIP:</strong> To prevent the pan from rusting, make sure your cast iron is "seasoned". Seasoning the cast iron means removing any excess moisture by setting it on the stove over high heat until all moisture has evaporated and coat with vegetable oil before storing.', 'Improving Cooking With Cookware', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'improving-cooking-cookware', '', '', '2016-03-16 20:45:47', '2016-03-16 20:45:47', '', 0, 'http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/?p=755', 0, 'post', '', 0),
