(1000, 1, '2016-07-28 17:16:14', '2016-07-28 17:16:14', '<h1 style="text-align: center;">9 Range Hood Safety Facts You Should Know About</h1>\r\n<h3 class="post-title"><em>Do I Absolutely Need a Range Hood? </em></h3>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Lato; font-size: 14px; line-height: 24px;">What do you know about range hood safety and the health benefits of having a range hood in your home? As consumers we want to know that the appliances we buy will not only be beautiful and have some great beneficial use, but we also want to know that these purchases will add value to our lives, especially considering the investment. Is safety something you consider before purchasing an appliance? Did you ever think that the appliances you buy could benefit your health, or possibly make your health worse? You probably haven''t thought of appliances in this way, and don''t feel bad because most of us only think of what good use we will get out of an appliance, and the appeal it will add to our space, and not the health benefits or health disadvantages that an appliance will have on us personally or on our family members considering that people spend so much of their time in their homes.</span></p>\r\nWith this being said, it is apparent that most people are not yet educated, or aware of the health benefits and safety factors of many appliances, with range hood safety being at the top of the list. So lets cut to the chase.. For those who think a range hood is just an unnecessary or so called expensive hood fan, that doesn''t do much of anything important, we think this statement could not be any more inaccurate or incorrect. In fact,  having a range hood not only adds some serious appeal to any kitchen space, while also getting rid of harsh odors, steam, and grease,  but it also does the most accurate job of eliminating toxic chemicals in the air that are created in our homes while cooking. If you have been asking yourself if having a range hood is important, we can assure you that when it comes to our health, a range hood is actually just as important as a diaper is to a baby,  or a sewage system is to a city, or gravity is to the atmosphere. But don''t take our word for it, lets jump into the facts..\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Range-hood-Safety-Importance-Infographic-01.jpg"><img class="wp-image-858 size-large aligncenter" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Range-hood-Safety-Importance-Infographic-01-1024x581.jpg" alt="range hood safety importance infographic proline range hoods" width="1024" height="581" /></a>\r\n\r\nThat''s not all, according to the American Lung Association, <strong>85 percent of Americans</strong> didn''t realize that the air in their homes was considered to be a legitimate health hazard that could possibly have short term or long term effects on their breathing, and if extreme enough can even be deathly. This is an even greater concern for those who already suffer from asthma or have poor breathing conditions already. This is also a legitimate health concern if you are currently  living in an older single-family home that was constructed before the 1970s. This is because these older homes are usually extremely airtight, and throughly insulated which increases indoor air quality problems as toxic chemicals will become more compacted into a smaller living space.\r\n<a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Range-hood-Safety-Importance-Infographic-05.jpg"><img class="wp-image-859 size-large aligncenter" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Range-hood-Safety-Importance-Infographic-05-1024x809.jpg" alt="range hood safety importance infographic proline range hoods" width="1024" height="809" /></a>\r\n\r\nYes, range hoods protect you and your family. This may sound extreme, especially considering that most people have not yet been informed on the effects of toxic chemicals released while cooking, and this is because research on this topic is still rather new. However, people are starting to become more aware of this health concern and many states throughout the U.S. have even put building codes in place requiring the installation of a range hood. According to ICC, <a href="http://publicecodes.cyberregs.com/icod/irc/2012/icod_irc_2012_15_sec003.htm"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Section M1503.4</strong> states; “Domestic kitchen cooking appliances shall be equipped with a ducted range hood." </span></a>\r\n\r\nWith cooking being something that most of us do everyday,  and with the new information and research we have access to, there is a new importance of having  safe indoor air quality in our homes. Well how can we stop problems like this and work to get rid of these health concerns? A simple way to do this is to purchase a powerful range hood with a higher CFM (cubic feet per minute). In regards to air cleanliness obviously the higher the CFM, the more efficient your hood fan will be in removing toxic chemicals in the air.  Yes, that also means that any range hood that comes equipped with more blower power, will also usually come with a greater purchase price.  However, it is important to keep in mind that when it comes to health and safety, there is peace of knowing that after purchasing a more powerful quality range hood, you can feel good to know that you will be breathing clean air everyday. This knew knowledge will easily change anyones perspective about the real value they are actually getting when purchasing a range hood. What was once thought to be just another expensive appliance, is now thought to be a great investment that will remove toxic chemicals from the air. In turn, this creates a healthier living environment for you.  If you are searching for a range hood and want to make sure you are purchasing a quality hood that actually works for more than making your kitchen smell better, make sure you check out our powerful selection of 1000+ CFM range hoods in our <a href="http://www.prolinerangehoods.com/index.php?main_page=index&amp;cPath=30_36">Proline Professional Range Hood Series</a> where you will surely find a hood that will sweep your air clean.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Range-hood-Safety-Importance-Infographic-04.jpg"><img class="wp-image-860 size-large aligncenter" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Range-hood-Safety-Importance-Infographic-04-1024x570.jpg" alt="range hood safety importance infographic proline range hoods" width="1024" height="570" /></a>\r\n\r\nYes, if you do not have a range hood, or do not use your range hood as often as you should, there is a good chance that these harsh chemicals are flying through your home.  However, not to worry because a range hood will be your best bet in removing these volatile air toxins. Keep in mind, that harsh chemicals are released from both electric and gas stoves due to non-stick coatings, cleaners, and other items used for cooking and cleaning and other factors. This is important to note, as both of these burners have their own associated health risks to take into account depending on how they are used.\r\n<h2>So why should we consider range hood safety as an important factor when purchasing a range hood and what are these so called harmful health effects?</h2>\r\nAccording to the <a href="http://www.doh.wa.gov/portals/1/Documents/Pubs/333-044.pdf">School of Indoor Air Quality Best Management Practices Manual</a> by participants in the Office of Environmental Health and Safety, the most commonly attributed health effects due to indoor air quality include:  Headache, fatigue, shortness of breath, sinus congestion, coughing, and sneezing. Some other common health effects include eye, nose, throat, and skin irritation, as well as dizziness and nausea. Cardiovascular disease,  chest pain, heart damage and even cancer have also been associated with exposure to indoor air contaminants. Infectious diseases such as the flu, or other viral infections can be much more easily spread through indoor air through personal contact. We find these health effects concerning, and that is why we choose to educate our customers about these health benefits of having a range hood before hand.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Range-hood-Safety-Importance-Infographic-02.jpg"><img class="wp-image-861 size-large aligncenter" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Range-hood-Safety-Importance-Infographic-02-1024x625.jpg" alt="range hood safety importance infographic proline range hoods" width="1024" height="625" /></a> <a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Range-hood-Safety-Importance-Infographic-03.jpg"><img class="wp-image-862 size-large aligncenter" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Range-hood-Safety-Importance-Infographic-03-1024x718.jpg" alt="range hood safety importance infographic proline range hoods" width="1024" height="718" /></a>\r\n\r\nOur goal is in no way to scare you, but to inform you about range hood safety and the true importance of having a range hood in your kitchen. If you are looking to purchase a range hood and don''t know where to begin, feel free to give us a call at <a href="tel:877-901-5530">877-901-5530</a> . We have a wonderful support team of experienced range hood professionals that will love to help you through any questions you may have.  You can also shoot us an email at <a href="mailto:support@prolinerangehoods.com">support@prolinerangehoods.com</a>.\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">Don''t forget to subscribe for more informative content, recipes, kitchen design tips and more!</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>-Your Friends At Proline</strong><a href="http://prolinerangehoods.com/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-863 size-large" src="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/Range-hood-Safety-Importance-Infographic-06-1024x470.jpg" alt="range hood safety importance infographic proline range hoods" width="1024" height="470" /></a></p>', '9 Range Hood Safety Facts You Should Know About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '848-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-28 17:16:14', '2016-07-28 17:16:14', '', 848, 'http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/848-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
