(995, 1, '2016-08-04 22:06:09', '2016-08-04 22:06:09', '<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Vent Hoods or OTR Microwaves for Kitchen Ventilation? Which is Best?</strong></h1>\r\n<h3 style="text-align: center;">When it comes to kitchen ventilation, there is an argument of which kitchen appliance is truly necessary. The more expensive vent hood, or the much less expensive OTR microwave?</h3>\r\nOh kitchen ventilation, why do you have to be so complicated? You are probably tired of the wild answers your a finding in online forums. Or maybe you are sick of the strong opinions you are getting from friends and family. Feel good to know that we know a lot about kitchen ventilation, and vent hoods are our jam! We have done our homework. We understand that kitchen ventilation is foreign to many since it''s not so commonly talked about.  Let us clear the air and just give it to you straight..\r\n\r\nFirst things first, lets jump into common statements you have probably heard before..\r\n<h4><em>You may have heard:</em></h4>\r\n<h3><strong>"A fan is a fan, they both do the exact same thing!"</strong></h3>\r\nOh dear, this is quite the assumption! However, this belief is much more common than you would think.\r\n\r\nOne problem with choosing an OTR microwave is the much smaller capture area. Have you ever cooked with an OTR microwave? When you did this, did you notice all of the steam, smoke and grease that gets so obviously missed? If microwave ventilation is missing what you can visually see, it''s not going to impress you with it''s ability of eliminating toxins and other chemicals in the air. Yes, those toxins that you so happen to be breathing in everyday? Unfortunately, when it comes to kitchen ventilation, this will most likely remain to be the case with an OTR microwave. Even with a more powerful OTR microwave, this still won''t manage to come close to cleaning the air efficiently enough. Keep in mind that even with range hoods, it it is always recommended to  <a href="http://www.prolinerangehoods.com/1-801-973-3959/support/common-questions/" target="_blank">try to size the hood 6” larger</a> in width than the cook top.\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to kitchen ventilation the the most effective option will always be a vent hood over an OTR microwave. There have been many recent studies on the importance of having a powerful vent hood installed in the home. This is due not only for effectiveness of use, but also due to the toxins and chemicals that are released in the air while cooking. Do you know how kitchen ventilation may affect your heath?  If  you aren''t sure how the quality of kitchen ventilation may directly affect your health, make sure to read <a href="http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/9-range-hood-safety-facts/" target="_blank">9 Range Hood Safety Facts You Should Know About</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>"My builder wants to charge me an outrageous amount to install a vent hood!"</strong></h3>\r\nThis is a common frustration that many new home owners face when it comes to kitchen ventilation.  However this does not mean that you can not shop around and see what you can find yourself. Get started by giving yourself a reasonable budget, &amp; do some vent hood shopping  online. After all, nobody will know how to spend your own money like you. However, when you start looking for better deals, make sure to not overlook quality, as this could cost you more in repairs later. You will be surprised to know that you will be able to find a range hood that is equally comparable in quality to top name brands such as Wolf and Viking, for a fraction of the price.\r\n\r\nYes, any vent hood that comes with a higher blower power will usually come with a greater price tag.  However, it is important to keep in mind that you are not just investing in a kitchen appliance. Most people cook and use their stoves several times a day. This directly effects our everyday life, and even our health, making kitchen ventilation essential.  After investing in a more powerful vent hood with a higher CFM, this means a more healthy &amp; clean living environment for you. This new understanding will easily change anyones perspective about the real value they are receiving. What was once thought to be just another expensive hood fan, is now thought to be a needed investment. If you are searching for a quality vent hood, make sure to check out Proline''s incredible selection of <a href="http://www.prolinerangehoods.com/index.php?main_page=index&amp;cPath=30_36" target="_blank">1000+ CFM vent hoods</a>.\r\n\r\nIn many states building codes have been set in place that require the proper installation of a kitchen vent hood. However, this is not necessarily the case in all states. Surprisingly, the installation of a vent hood is not required everywhere. This leaves consumers with the assumption that a range hood is not needed because it''s not required.\r\n\r\nBuilding codes are put in place  for your safety, health, and general welfare. They are only created with our best interest in mind. However, before assuming that a range hood is not needed, you should understand  a few things. Firstly, that <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Building_code">building codes</a> only specify the <strong>MINIMUM</strong> standards. Meaning, they are as lenient as they can be.  We feel that leniency is not an option when it comes to things such as cleanliness &amp; safety.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong>"I found an OTR Microwave with with a 400 CFM (Cubic Feet per Minute) vent!"</strong></h3>\r\nThe problem with over-the-range-microwaves is that they don''t vent to the efficiency that is needed. This remains the case even if they are vented to the outside.  This is because with OTR microwaves, the  CFM is very low. The CFM is the measurement of the velocity at which air flows into/out of a space. The highest CFM you will normally find with an OTR microwave is 300 CFM to 400 CFM which is not powerful enough.\r\n<h4><strong>Take Note: Let''s compare OTR microwaves to what professionals in the industry recommend..</strong></h4>\r\nIt is standard in the industry to recommend at least  600 CFM. OTR microwaves are simply not strong enough at doing the kitchen ventilation job that it is needed. The higher the CFM rating, the more efficient the job when removing toxic chemicals, grease, steam, and harsh smells. For this reason, professionals recommend to choose a dedicated vent hood option with a higher blower power.\r\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Solution: Get the Hood!</strong></span></h3>\r\nWe hope you found this post to be helpful and informative. Make sure to subscribe to keep up to date with the greatest tips and kitchen design ideas.\r\n<h3><strong> </strong></h3>', 'Let''s Talk Kitchen Ventilation | Vent Hood or OTR Microwaves?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'vent-hood-microwave-kitchen-ventilation', '', '\nhttp://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/9-range-hood-safety-facts/', '2016-08-05 14:54:14', '2016-08-05 14:54:14', '', 0, 'http://www.prolinekitchenblog.com/?p=995', 0, 'post', '', 0),
